channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: A Police Officer Who Rescued a Baby in a Box Reunites With Him 24-Years Later
Read the transcript of President Bidenâ€™s first post-debate interview
item.description: Read the full transcript of President Biden's first sit-down interview since his disastrous debate performance against former President Trump last week.

item.title: Ric Grenell to Newsmax: D.C. Looks Like 'Hunger Games'
item.description: Former acting Director of National Intelligence Richard Grenell told Newsmax on Friday that Washington, D.C., with its skyscrapers and continued tug on taxpayers' wallets looks like something out of a dystopian movie.

item.title: WATCH: Joe Biden's Big Interview With George Stephanopoulos Is Out, and It's an Absolute Trainwreck
Biden blames Trump's 'shouting' for debate debacle despite no evidence it occurred
item.description: President Biden said during his ABC News interview former President Trump's "shouting" during last week's debate "distracted" him, worsening his performance.

item.title: Rep. Owens to Newsmax: We Don't Have Leader in White House
item.description: Rep. Burgess Owens, R-Utah, told Newsmax on Friday that in light of the revelations regarding President Joe Biden's mental acuity, "it's obvious we do not have a leader in the White House."

item.title: Biden Flips Out on Reporters When They Ask Whether He Should Continue in Race
Combative Biden refuses to quit 2024 race, dismisses polls and mental acuity questions in pivotal interview
item.description: President Biden, 81, sat for an interview with ABC News Friday night after his disastrous debate performance against former President Trump.

item.title: Former RNC Chair: How Can Trump Disagree With Project 2025?
item.description: Former Republican National Committee Chair Michael Steele expressed outrage amid former President Trump's attempt to distance himself from the conservative policy plan known as Project 2025 on Friday.

item.title: Oklahoma's Supreme Court Bans Catholic Charter School in Seeming Defiance of the Supreme Court
Biden repeatedly dodges questions about whether he'd take neurological test: 'No one said I had to'
item.description: President Biden dodged questions about whether he'd take a neurological test in one of the most contentious moments of his first sit-down interview since his presidential debate.

item.title: Rep. Van Drew to Newsmax: I 'Support' Garland Arrest
item.description: Rep. Jeff Van Drew, R-N.J., told Newsmax on Friday he would "support" an "inherent contempt" vote of Attorney General Merrick Garland in the House.

item.title: Cat Scratch Fever - How to Prevent Your Feline Shredder From Attacking Furniture
Biden takes blame for 'bad night' in debate against Trump: 'My fault, no one else's fault'
item.description: President Biden is facing intense scrutiny about his health and viability as a presidential candidate as he sits down with ABC News anchor George Stephanopoulos.

item.title: Biden WH Decries Hungary PM Orban's Visit to Moscow
item.description: The White House on Friday criticized Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orban's trip to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin in Moscow, saying it will "neither advance the cause of peace, nor will it promote Ukrainian sovereignty."
